'''Erien''' was the daughter of [[Fingon]] according to a very late, but ultimately rejected version of the [[legendarium]].<ref name="Shib">{{PM|XINotes}}, Note 35, p. 361</ref>

She had one other sibling, a brother called [[Finbor]].<ref name="Shib"/>

== Etymology ==
The name ''Erien'' is in [[Sindarin]], but it has no clear meaning. A possible explanation of her name would be a combination of the Sindarin adjective ''[[er]]'' ("one, alone") + the feminine suffix ''[[-ien]]''.<ref>{{webcite|author=[[Paul Strack]]|articleurl=https://eldamo.org/content/words/word-1002707959.html|articlename=S. ''Erien'' pn.|website=Eldamo|accessed=07 August 2023}}</ref>

An earlier, rejected form of her name was ''Ernis''.<ref name="Shib"/>

